FT  18 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Cheam
Cheam Group, the south-west London and Surrey water supply company, lifted
turnover by 13 per cent and pre-tax profits by 20 per cent during the 12
months to March 31.
The pre-tax line improved from Pounds 3.31m to Pounds 3.98m, on turnover of
Pounds 15.6m (Pounds 13.7m).
Earnings per share worked through at 41.9p (37.2p) and a recommended final
dividend of 9.3p brings the total for the year to 14p (11p).
